FastStream is an open-source framework for building asynchronous web services that interact with event streams. It simplifies the creation of producers and consumers for message queues, automates parsing, networking, and documentation generation, and streamlines workflows to accelerate progress. FastStream supports multiple message brokers like Kafka, RabbitMQ, NATS, and Redis, and integrates with HTTP frameworks, especially FastAPI. It offers features like Pydantic validation, automatic AsyncAPI documentation, powerful dependency injection, and is optimized for automatic code generation with models like GPT and Llama.
